"{\"uid\": \"connexionfrance.com-news-local-police-to-join-strike-action-during-paris-olympics-661687\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Subscribe to The Connexion  See prices & plans  HELP GUIDES  Income Tax in France  Healthcare in France  Inheritance Law and Wills in France  Visas and residency cards for France  Subscribe to The Connexion  See prices & plans  HELP GUIDES  Income Tax in France  Healthcare in France  Inheritance Law and Wills in France  Visas and residency cards for France  Sign up here        Police unions have declared a nationwide strike from July 14 to August 15, potentially disrupting the progress of the Olympic torch and the running of the Olympic Games themselves.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 75, \"end\": 81, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 97, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 134, \"end\": 140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 172, \"end\": 178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 255, \"end\": 261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 352, \"end\": 358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read also:Day by day: Where Olympic torch will pass in France on way to Paris  They are striking to seek a reevaluation of their professional status in the eyes of the government, which is unchanged since 1999, as well as denouncing the conditions of their retirement.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 617, \"end\": 623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 634, \"end\": 639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4331082702445671e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is scandalous that some municipal police officers are retiring at the age of 64 with a pension below the poverty line,\\\" the unions said in a signed declaration, who claim that the government is hearing but not listening to them.\", \"from\": 832, \"to\": 1064, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris mairie is struggling to recruit police officers for the Olympics, now relying on 2,000 officers rather than the 5,000 originally promised by mayor of Paris, Anne Hidalgo.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1070, \"end\": 1075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4331082702445671e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1226, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4331082702445671e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1233, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"45,000 police officers and gendarmes will be deployed on July 26 for the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:UPDATED: Strikes in France in June 2024 and how you may be impacted  It is unclear what the repercussions of this strike will be.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999996871338, \"rank\": 1.8556787006435055e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Active national police officers are not allowed to go on strike but there is no legislation surrounding the right to strike of local police officers.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More industries may also go on strike during the Olympics, such as the binmen of Paris, hotel workers and security guards, to protest the reform of unemployment benefits.\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4331082702445671e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Workers in these industries \\\"cannot be blamed\\\" for going on strike, said the secretary-general of the Conf\\u00e9d\\u00e9ration g\\u00e9n\\u00e9rale du travail (General Confederation of Labour) Sophie Binet.\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_(France)\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Conf\\u00e9d\\u00e9ration g\\u00e9n\\u00e9rale du travail\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q178790\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/General_Confederation_of_Labour_(France)\"}, {\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"score\": 0.5845989114465986, \"rank\": 0.702040430250405, \"text\": \"Sophie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Scholl\"}, {\"begin\": 1980, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/r